  "text": "Molecular epidemiology studies of HIV-1 indicate that the epidemic in Brazil is complex and diverse: subtype B is predominant in the country except in the southern region, where subtype C prevails [CITATION_1] . Among pregnant women, recent molecular data from central Brazil have shown an unexpectedly high prevalence of subtype C viruses, which are strongly related to those circulating in southern/southeastern Brazil [CITATION_2] .",
